  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Combatting Modern Slavery in Mining Sites in North and South Kivu</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The overall project objective is to contribute to improving stability and access to human rights in and around mining areas in the Eastern Democratic Republic of the Congo (DRC) through interventions seeking to curb the prevalence of modern slavery, with a focus on vulnerable women and children.  The interventions seek to contribute to develop the capacities of local authorities, the civil society and artisanal mining operators, as well as strengthening coordination mechanisms to effectively combat modern slavery in mining supply chains. This combination of community-based and government-led approaches is being employed to enhance project effectiveness and sustainability based on the lessons learned and strategic needs identified during previous and ongoing programming. This project additionally contributes to the goal of the Government of DRC to achieve mandatory due diligence obligations in the mining sector while simultaneously contributing to training and awareness raising on the prevention of trafficking in persons, detecting, investigating, and prosecuting traffickers, as well as protection and assistance to victims and witnesses.</narrative>
  </description>
